modules.description: Generates stubs for JavaScript interop based on a boolean reference and retrieves them as an array of strings. It sets a custom timer function that returns a float and enables debug logging for JSOO with a specified message and flag. The module interacts directly with runtime state and debugging features.

Handles JavaScript object interaction through methods for property access, function invocation, and value conversion. Operates on OCaml values that represent JavaScript objects, arrays, and primitives. Enables direct manipulation of DOM elements and browser APIs from OCaml code.

Manages JavaScript interop by generating and retrieving stubs, and controls runtime behavior through custom timers and debug logging. It manipulates a boolean reference to conditionally generate code and exposes a float-returning timer function. Debug messages can be selectively enabled with a flag, allowing fine-grained control over JSOO output. Examples include dynamically generating JS bindings and instrumenting runtime performance.

Provides functions to execute code cells and generate HTML representations of their status. Operates on a status type that pairs a string identifier with a string result, and processes raw code strings to produce structured output. Used to run and display the outcome of individual code snippets in a controlled environment.
